On-screen text & graphics_caption: Happy gotcha day to my best friend and soul dog 🧡 Sharing a little bit of the lore behind Clementine’s name in honor of today and Lana’s new song ‘Stars Fell on Alabama’ 🍊💫✨
Audio & prosody_summary: The audio features a melancholic song with a male vocalist accompanied by piano and guitar, later joined by a female vocalist and more orchestral elements. The lyrics express feelings of luck and admiration, creating a reflective and calm atmosphere.
On-screen text & graphics_on_screen_text: Four years ago today, I flew from Arizona to Alabama to bring home a tiny 2lb mini dachshund puppy I had been dreaming about for years...I named her Clementine, after a Lana Del Rey song that referenced a daughter named Clementine, and the character Clementine Kruczynzki from Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless MindShe brought so much love and light into my life during a really dark time for me. I've never been an "everything happens for a reason" kind of person, but I truly believe we were meant to find each other.Her name was always very meaningful to me, but as she grew up and our life changed, the connections and synchronicities between her name, our life together, Lana's work, and Eternal Sunshine became even stronger.We moved to the Bay Area after a big life change and I found even more connections to the song Clementine was named after 'Dance Till We Die' and the Bay Area and our life in CaliforniaI reread Lana's poetry book 'Violet Bent Backwards Over the Grass', and felt deeply connected to one poem in particular called 'What Happened When I Left You' that referenced Eternal Sunshine. It all felt very aligned and meaningfulThen in April at Stagecoach, Lana performed a new song called 'Stars Fell on Alabama' that referenced Clementine for the second time. Clementine was born in Alabama so it felt very serendipitous yet againAll this to say, happy gotcha day to my soulmate, my Eternal Sunshine, my Clementine 🍊
